column5: Does this mean anything? Sorry, I'm a little slow at times.
The closest thing to sitting in front of the stage at a peeler joint.
Man that was a long time ago. 3 for a dollar in 1980 !
Used to pay 25 cents in Hamilton on the 70's.....I did have to wash the glass myself though,,
When I was stationed in Halifax in the mid 60's the Stadacona Naval Base had a pub and Friday night was nickle night.  You could go in with a dollar and party all evening
Are you guys talking about beer or dances?
You only need beer to mask the unpretty ones.   Then when the lights come on, oh what did I get myself into.
I remember a tray at the Conroy,$10, 30 glasses,every one bought a round,you were a different person when you left lol
Yah.. that's three for a dollar Davey!
Good time Wayne,super cheap.1982 if I remember,33cents a glass
Men"s room,at the time and busy,plus you could not see your exit for the smoke lol.Always Thursday night
you could not see your exit for the smoke lol.  Ah yes, the good ole days LOL
